Patch Set 19: Code-Review+1
looks fine to me.  also needs a rebase
Does it make sense to define gpio polarity as 'unknown' ?

On entity-manager schema side it doesn't make much sense, so i am fine to drop it from this schema enum. But on client side i would need this to initialize the vars to defaults, so it makes sense to keep them in configuration PDI.
if 'DefaultAction' is not a required property, why is there an option to define it as unknown?
In schema, yes, its not a required property so i am fine to drop it.
Is GPIOLeakDetector a subtype of the leak_detector? Should we make it generic and extendable to other type of leak_detector in the future?
The GPIOLeakDetector is the one which implements the GPIO hardware interface. So, its a specific kind, so i don't think we need to make it extendable.
@Zhikui Please let me know if you have any other question on this comment, otherwise i will mark it resolved. Thanks
was there some discussion somewhere on using these PDI prefixes on everything?  Both Polarity and GpioPolarity have already been in the schema for quite some time.

Until now, none of the Configuration interfaces were documented in PDI. I have created a PDI PR for this https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/75999/comments/21a1bfb9_04f82e2d and its being discussed there.

Please write this patchset using the existing style of enumeration.  If we end up making PDI compliant dbus interfaces, we're not going to (by design intent of EM) be propagating them to the EM configs files themselves.
Based on the discussion on discord https://discord.com/channels/775381525260664832/867820390406422538/1317305700271263816, changing these enum values to non-namespace values.
@Ed @Matt @Zhikui I have addressed and replied to your comments. Can you please let me know if you have any other comments?
We don't crossreference Redfish here.  Make this a proper enumeration of the two types (or for now just assume Moisture, as I don't know of any BMCs with FloatSwitch leak detectors)

Sure, i have dropped redfish reference from description and added 3 values -
- Moisture
- LeakSensingCable (Meta has a use case for this and i have requested Redfish to add it).
- Unknown

Please let me know if any other question?

In latest patch, i updated to only 2 values as @Patrick asked me earlier to only include what is being implemented -

* LeakSensingCable (Meta has a use case for this and i have requested Redfish to add it).
* Unknown

Please let me know if any other question?

Please remove the PDI-style namespacing from all of these.  If we're going to support PDI, that's fine, but the EM config files and schema shouldn't need PDI definitions in them to do it, otherwise we break the rule of "You don't need to be a dbus expert to write an EM config file".
Based on the discussion on discord https://discord.com/channels/775381525260664832/867820390406422538/1317305700271263816, changing these enum values to non-namespace values.
What does this mean?  This should likely not be configurable, right?  There's no such thing as a "warning" leak detector.
Please refer to requirement#2 in design https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/73152/15/designs/liquid-leak-detection.md#30
